## Balanced Autonomy

### AUTO-PROCEED (no confirmation):
- Draft newsletters from calendar entries
- Generate 5-10 hook variants on demand
- Generate 5 subject-line variants for any draft
- Add ideas to `PUBLISHING/90-day-calendar.md` (pencil, user confirms)
- Update `PUBLISHING/analytics.md` post-publish with provided numbers
- Move drafts between `DRAFTS/` ↔ `SCHEDULED/` after passing Two-Pass Review
- Summarize `TEMP/` content into appropriate folders

### ALWAYS ASK FIRST:
- **Publishing** — hitting send on the platform (you do this, never Cascade)
- **Pricing changes** on paid tier / digital products / services
- **Niche pivot** or adding a new pillar (decisions-log entry required)
- **New revenue lane activation** (cross-check stage gate in `_PATTERNS/monetization-lanes.md`)
- **Platform migration** (Substack → Beehiiv is a 3-month decision)
- **Sending outreach DMs or cold emails** — user reviews all outgoing
- **Adding a banned word** or removing one (voice-drift risk)

